<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-056-028 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 347 821</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 23 1991 n660 p72(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Planning mil-ASIC strategy. (military application-specificintegrated circuits) (part of an annual report on the military)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lawrence, James L. III.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The military electronics industry is expected to experience growthinto the next century, but attention must be paid to commercialmarkets, costs and the viability of new technologies.andO;Application-specific integrated circuits (ASICs) are particularlysuited for this market.andP;  Military ASIC designers need to developstrategic partnerships with their suppliers or they will findtheir systems obsolete within a few years.andP;  Military contractorsare forced to pay attention to development and procurement costs.andO;Strategic plans should include the economic climate anddesigner/ASIC supplier partnerships.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MilitaryWeapons IndustryStrategic PlanningResearch and DevelopmentHigh TechnologyMarketingApplication-Specific Integrated CircuitsEconomics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>